(7, 'Program Sarjana', 'Undergraduate Program', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Program Sarjana</a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Kurikulum untuk Program Sarjana</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Mayor Proteksi Tanaman</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Departemen Proteksi Tanaman</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Fakultas Pertanian, Institut Pertanian Bogor</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Kurikulum dalam proteksi tanaman di disain untuk memberikan latar belakang yang kuat dalam ilmu pengendalian hama dan penyakit dengan menekankan pada hama dan penyakit tanaman.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Sasaran Program</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Program sarjana dengan Mayor Proteksi Tanaman diarahkan untuk menghasilkan lulusan pertanian yang profesional di bidang perlindungan tanaman panen. Lulusan ini diharapkan mampu dalam (1) identifikasi, analisa, dan mengatasi berbagai masalah hama dan penyakit tumbuhan; (2) mengelola ekosistem pertanian dengan mengaplikasikan teknologi perlindungan tanaman ramah lingkungan; (3) mengaplikasikan dan mengomunikasikan pengetahuan dan keterampilan mereka dalam tempat kerja mereka; (4) mendemonstrasikan keterampilan yang dapat dibagikan termasuk keterampilan komunikasi, manajemen data, dan teknologi informasi; (5) berkompetisi di pasar tenaga kerja di dalam dan di luar negeri.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Syarat untuk Memperoleh Gelar</strong><strong></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Mahasiswa sarjana diharuskan untuk menyelesaikan minimal 144 SKS untuk memperoleh gelar, termasuk seminar dan proyek penelitian sarjana.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Gelar yang Diberikan</strong><strong></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Mahasiswa yang telah menuntaskan sebuah mayor sarjana di proteksi tanaman diberikan gelar Bachelor of Agricultural Science atau <em>Sarjana Pertanian</em>.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Disain Mata Kuliah</strong><strong></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">Mata kuliah mayor proteksi tanaman diklasifikasikan menjadi (a) mata kuliah umum (14 mata kuliah, 36 SKS), (b) mata kuliah yang diperlukan, diambil dari departemen lain atau dikenal sebagai mata kuliah interdepartemen (14 mata kuliah, 44 SKS); dan (c) mata kuliah mayor yang diperlukan di proteksi tanaman (18 mata kuliah termasuk seminar dan tugas akhir, 51 SKS) diambil dari Departemen Proteksi Tanaman (PTN). Sebagai tambahan, mahasiswa wajib mengambil mata kuliah minor atau mata kuliah pendukung (<em>supporting courses</em>) (15 SKS)</span></p>', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Undergraduate Program</a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Curriculum for the Undergraduate Program</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Majoring in Plant Protection</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Department of Plant Protection</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Faculty of Agriculture, Bogor Agricultural University</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Curriculum is one of the modalities that determine the quality of an educational program.&nbsp; Quality of an academic program cannot be separated from the problem of relevance.&nbsp; Any attempt towards creating quality education cannot disregard relevance of the program being implemented.&nbsp; Considering this matter, we carefully develop curriculum which would make the academic program in plant protection relevant to the present and future conditions.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The staff of the Department of Plant Protection have designed the curriculum in plant protection in such a way that</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(a). It provides the students with the knowledge and skills appropriate for developing successful careers at the farmer level, in governmental institutions, research and development sectors as well as in the industrial world;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(b). The students acquire all the basic sciences needed for future development of the field of study;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(c). It is feasible time-wise and resource-wise so that it can be followed effectively by the students within the proposed length of study;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(d). It is relevant to the current and future needs of the students as an individual and as a member of a society;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(e). The students have a scientific mind as well as empathy towards the society.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Many people have always viewed a curriculum as a list of courses, and renewing a curriculum as a matter of adding new courses, and if necessary, dropping the old ones. &nbsp;This is indeed a false understanding of curriculum.&nbsp; In the Department of Plant Protection, we view the curriculum not as a mere list of courses, instead it is a structure which is founded upon a chosen design.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In this way a curricular structure can be envisaged as a building with a number of compartments.&nbsp; Each time we wish to introduce an innovation, an enrichment, or even an overall revision, what we have to do is to describe the nature of the change we wish to make, and to break it down into several components.&nbsp; In this way, a new subject matter can be introduced into the curriculum without adding a new course, but merely by making changes in the substance of a number of courses within the various compartments of the curriculum.&nbsp; The staff of the Department of Plant Protection have been using this approach in building the curriculum in plant protection.&nbsp; The curriculum is based on a solid foundation, but it is dynamic so that it can respond to the changes and challenges we are facing in the academic life.&nbsp; By adopting such approach we hope that we can prepare our graduates to face the competition and challenges in the future.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong>Objective of the Program</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The undergraduate program with Plant Protection Major is aimed at producing professional agricultural graduates in the field of crop protection.&nbsp; The graduates are expected to be capable in (1) identifying, analyzing, and solving plant pest and disease problems; (2) managing agricultural ecosystems by applying environmentally-friendly crop protection technology; (3) applying and communicating their knowledge and skills in their workplace; (4) demonstrating transferable skills including communication skill, data management, and information technology; (5) competing in domestic and foreign labor market.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Requirement for the Degree</strong><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The undergraduate students are required to complete a minimum of 144 credits of courses for the degree, including Undergraduate Seminar and Research Project.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Awarded Degree</strong><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Students completing an undergraduate major in plant protection are awarded the Bachelor of Agricultural Science or <em>Sarjana Pertanian</em> degree.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Course Design</strong><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The plant protection major courses are classified as (a) general courses (14 courses, 36 credits), (b) required courses taken from other departments known as interdepartmental courses (14 courses, 44 credits); and (c) required major courses of plant protection (18 courses including seminar and final task, 51 credits) taken at the Department of Plant Protection (DPP). &nbsp;In addition, the students have to take minor courses or supporting courses (15 credits).&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>', '2011-08-18 10:38:28', 1),
(8, 'Fasilitas Gedung', 'Building Facilities', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Fasilitas Gedung</a></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%;" lang="IN">Departemen Proteksi Tanaman menempati gedung utama seluas 7,653 </span><span style="line-height: 115%;">m<sup>2 </sup>&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 115%;" lang="IN">di kompleks Fakultas Pertanian.</span></span></li>\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span lang="IN">Laboratorium Komputer terhubung dengan LAN dan sistem Internet tersedia guna kegiatan pendidikan dan penelitian untuk seluruh anggota mahasiswa dan staf pengajar.</span></span></li>\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span lang="IN">Perpustakaan Departemen terletak di lantai pertama gedung utama dan menyediakan koleksi referensi terdiri atas lebih dari 1800 judul buku pelajaran dan lebih dari 75 jurnal ilmiah termasuk jurnal <em>on-line.</em></span></span></li>\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span lang="IN">Berbagai laboratorium Penelitian terdiri atas 6 laboratorium entomologi/rodentologi dan 5 laboratorium patologi tumbuhan. Peralatan modern dan maju tersedia guna mendukung berbagai aktivitas penelitian.</span></span></li>\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span lang="IN">Empat Laboratorium Pendidikan terletak di lantai pertama gedung utama dan telah berperalatan lengkap guna kerja praktikum.</span></span></li>\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Departemen Proteksi tanaman memiliki fasilitas penelitian lapang (&plusmn; 2 ha) dan 4 unit rumah kaca yang terletak di kompleks <em>University Farm</em> sekitar 1.5 km dari<em> </em>gedung utama departemen.</span></li>\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Departemen memiliki koleksi serangga dan penyakit dan&nbsp; yang besar. Museum &nbsp;serangga departemen atau dikenal sebagai <em>Insect Teaching Collection</em> (ITC) terdapat koleksi serangga guna mendukung berbagai aktivitas pendidikan, pembelajaran, dan penelitian. Unit ini merupakan bagian dari eduwisata universitas dan terbuka untuk masyarakat umum.</span></li>\n</ul>', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/folder_32.png" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> Building Facilities </a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">The Department of Plant Protection occupies a 7,653 m2&nbsp; main building in the Faculty of&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acriculture complex.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Laboratory of Computers connected with LAN and Internet system is available for&nbsp; teaching and research activities&nbsp;&nbsp; for all students and faculty members.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">The Departmental library is housed in the first floor of the main building and provides reference collection consisting of more than 1800 titles of text books and more than 75 scientific journals including on-line journals.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Research laboratories are composed of 5 entomology, 1 rodentology and 5 plant pathology laboratories.&nbsp;&nbsp; Modern and advanced equipments are available to support research activities.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Four teaching laboratories are located on the first floor of the main building and are well equipped for practical works.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">The&nbsp; Department&nbsp; of&nbsp; Plant&nbsp; Protection has a field&nbsp; research&nbsp; facility (&plusmn; 2 ha) and 4 units of greenhouse located in the University Farm complex about 1.5 km from the departmental&nbsp; main building.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Department has a large insect and disease collection.</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">These collection provides an execellent materials for teaching, training, research, and outraech program.</span></li>\n</ul>', '2011-08-18 09:50:51', 4),
(9, 'Pestisida Baru', 'New Pestiside', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Pestisida Baru</a></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">ada pestisida baru ber-merk blue magic .</span></p>', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;New Pesticide</a></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">there is new pestiside named blue magic.</span></p>', '2011-07-26 15:28:44', 3),
