(29, 'Aktivitas Riset', 'Research Activity', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Aktivitas Riset</a></h2>\n<h3 style="text-align: center;" align="center">&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3 style="text-align: center;" align="center"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">CENTER FOR INTEGRATED PEST MANAGEMENT</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">(CFIPM-IPB)</span></h3>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Kampus IPB Darmaga, Jl. Kamper, Bogor 16680, INDONESIA</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Phone: +62-0251-8629363 Fax.: +62-0251-8629-363 </span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">E-mail: <a href="mailto:pkpht@indo.net.id">pkpht@indo.net.id</a></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Research Activities</a></h2>\n<h3 align="center">&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3 align="center"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">CENTER FOR INTEGRATED PEST MANAGEMENT</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">(CFIPM-IPB)</span></h3>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Kampus IPB Darmaga, Jl. Kamper, Bogor 16680, INDONESIA</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Phone: +62-0251-8629363 Fax.: +62-0251-8629-363 </span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">E-mail: <a href="mailto:pkpht@indo.net.id">pkpht@indo.net.id</a></span></p>\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Introduction</span></h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;" align="justify"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For more than thirty years, scientists from the Department of Plant Pests and Diseases Faculty of Agriculture - Bogor Agricultural University have been a leader in the country&rsquo;s research activities related to pest and disease ecology, systematic, morphology, physiology and pest management.</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Today, its 47 staff members are expanding its research focus to include the development of pest control technologies that would ensure sustainability as well as the safety of agricultural products and the environment.&nbsp; A wide variety of research topics in biological control, habitat management, plant virology, insecticide toxicology, nematology, insect diversity and systematics, are just a few examples of research interests of the Department.</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understanding changes and the challenges they bring have been one of the strength of the Department.&nbsp; It is this awareness also that made the Department launched the Center for Integrated Pest Management (CFIPM) on February 24, 1997. The development of CFIPM has been forced by the increased need to produce quality research and qualified human resources for the development of the country in the midst of the global changes the world is facing.&nbsp; We, in the Center understand the importance of education and research and thus the primary goal of the Center is human resource development in IPM-related disciplines.</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Through the establishment of the CFIPM, the Department continues to lead the way in scientific excellence through the expansion&nbsp; of its programs to address key issues of today.&nbsp; The Center, drawing its strength from nine different laboratories, strives to integrate training, teaching, basic as well as applied research, and services, that would enhance plant protection techniques in Indonesia for the future generations.</span><br /><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Center has produced this book with two major goals.&nbsp; The first is to inform potential collaborators whether individuals, institutions, or organizations of the specific kinds of research that the Center undertakes and of the personnel that it brings to bear on the above challenge.&nbsp; The second purpose is to inform potential students, visiting scientists and other interested individuals of the research activities that are conducted in the Center.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;" align="justify"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><br /></span></p>\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Vision</span></h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Vision of CFIPM is to become a center of excellence in the development of Indonesian human resources through discovery, development, improvement and dissemination of science, technology and arts of pest management and its supporting disciplines directed towards improvement of the society&rsquo;s welfare.</span></p>\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Mission</span></h3>\n<ol>\n<li style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">To achieve excellence in research and education of IPM-related fields.</span></li>\n<li style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">To participate actively as an agent of development.&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li style="margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">To develop international quality graduate education in IPM-related disciplines to support sustainable agriculture production system using improvement of integrative university research as an entry point.</span></li>\n</ol>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Scope of Program</span></h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To run its mission, CFIPM designs quality programs. The programs are divided into three major activities:</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><br /></span></p>\n<h4 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">I.&nbsp; Education</span></h4>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Center works closely with the Entomology-Phytopathology (ENT-FIT) Graduate Study Program to increase the quality of teaching and education conducted.&nbsp; In the last 5 years the ENT-FIT study program accepted 96 students pursuing Masters and Doctorate degrees in three different areas: Entomology, Plant Pathology and Integrated Pest Management.&nbsp; To support their study, CIFPM has increased the quality of laboratory and library facilities by investing in books, journals, Internet and equipment&rsquo;s pertinent to the latest technologies.&nbsp; At the moment there are 28 academic staffs who are actively teaching the Graduate Program, 26 of them holding Ph.D. degree from international universities such as USA, England, France, Germany, Japan, Australia and The Philippines.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><br /></span></p>\n<h4 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">II.&nbsp;&nbsp; Research</span></h4>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In last three years, there are 52 research project conducted in the center. These research projects are funded by various national as well as international funding agencies and projects such as University Research for Graduate Education (URGE) project, Directorate General of Higher Education (DGHE), Ministry of Research and Technology, ARMP, ACIAR, Wildlife Preservation Trust International (WPTI), National Research Council-Germany, Tokyo University of Agriculture (TUA-Japan), Whitley, UNEP, Basic Research Grant, Integrated Research Grant, International Toray Science Foundation, and BIOTROP.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><br /></span></p>\n<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">III. Training and Workshops</span></h3>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To improve the quality of human resource, various training and workshops have been conducted by the Center. The training and workshops that have been conducted include:</span></p>\n<ol>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on identification of scale insects, aphids and whiteflies</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on mushroom cultivation</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on plant pest and disease management in horticulture.</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on development and utilization of natural insecticides</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on application of molecular techniques in the detection and diagnosis of plant viruses</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on scientific writings.</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training and workshop on Plant Clinic management and the application of molecular detection techniques in diagnosis of&nbsp; plant pests and diseases.</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on development and utilization of parasitoids (exploration, identification, and field release).</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on molecular marker techniques for the study of insect population</span></li>\n<li style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 30px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Training on molecular techniques for the plant pathogen detection.</span></li>\n</ol>\n<p style="text-align: justify; margin-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>', '2011-08-18 11:04:49', 1),
(30, 'Ekspedisi Ulat Bulu', 'Expedition Caterpillar Hairs', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #cccccc;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#">&nbsp; Berita</a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<center><img style="border: 8px solid #ccc;" src="images/ulbul.jpg" alt="Example pic" width="574px" height="250px" /></center>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: medium;">Ekspedisi Ulat Bulu</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Akhir-akhir ini ulat bulu menjadi salah satu primadona yang banyak dibicarakan dalam berbagai media massa maupun forum ilmiah. Pertama kali wabah ulat bulu melanda warga di tujuh desa di Probolinggo, Jawa Timur. Selanjutnya serangan ulat bulu juga meresahkan warga di daerah Jakarta, hingga saat ini serangan ulat bulu telah melanda di beberapa daerah di Pulau Jawa dan Bali. Beberapa media massa menyampaikan bahwa ulat bulu telah menyebar dari Probolinggo ke daerah lain termasuk Jakarta. Padahal fakta dari hasil ekspedisi sementara tim Proteksi Tanaman IPB, ulat bulu di daerah Probolinggo dan Jakarta itu berbeda spesies.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Ada berbagai dugaan faktor pemicu terjadinya ledakan ulat bulu di beberapa tempat. Menurut Prof. Dr. Ir. Aunu Rauf. MSc, salah satu faktornya adalah adanya musim hujan yang berkepanjangan mengakibatkan parasitoid atau musuh alami dari ulat bulu tidak mampu bertahan hidup, sehingga populasi ulat bulu meningkat drastis. Selain itu, adanya migrasi ngengat (imago ulat bulu) dari habitatnya menuju pemukiman warga, karena habitat asalnya telah rusak.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Serangan ulat bulu ini telah mengakibatkan banyak pihak menjadi khawatir dan resah. Berbagai upaya pengendalian telah dilakukan oleh warga, pemerintah daerah, dan beberapa instansi yang terkait, mulai dari pengendalian mekanis dengan diambil secara manual, pengendalian hayati dengan penggunaan predator, hingga pengendalian kimiawi dengan penyemprotan insektisida sintetik.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Adanya fenomena ulat bulu ini bukanlah ancaman, tetapi menjadi tantangan bagi tim ekspedisi Proteksi Tanaman IPB untuk menemukan berbagai potensi pengendalian yang akan dipadukan dalam suatu pengendalian hama terpadu (PHT) yang efektif dalam mengendalikan hama ulat bulu dan aman bagi ekosistem alami.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">(Herma Amalia)</span></p>', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#">&nbsp; News</a></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<center><img style="border: 8px solid #ccc;" src="images/ulbul.jpg" alt="Example pic" width="574px" height="250px" /></center>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: medium;">Expedition Caterpillar Hairs</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id="result_box" class="long_text" style="font-size: small; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Akhir-akhir ini ulat bulu menjadi salah satu primadona yang banyak dibicarakan dalam berbagai media massa maupun forum ilmiah.">Lately caterpillars become one of the belle of the much talked about in various mass media and scientific forums. </span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Pertama kali wabah ulat bulu melanda warga di tujuh desa di Probolinggo, Jawa Timur.">The first time outbreaks of caterpillars hit residents in seven villages in Probolinggo, East Java. </span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Selanjutnya serangan ulat bulu juga meresahkan warga di daerah Jakarta, hingga saat ini serangan ulat bulu telah melanda di beberapa daerah di Pulau Jawa dan Bali.">Further attacks caterpillars are also disturbing residents in the Jakarta area, up to now attack the caterpillars have been hit in some areas in Java and Bali. </span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Beberapa media massa menyampaikan bahwa ulat bulu telah menyebar dari Probolinggo ke daerah lain termasuk Jakarta.">Some media said that the caterpillars have spread to other areas of Probolinggo, including Jakarta. </span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Padahal fakta dari hasil ekspedisi sementara tim Proteksi Tanaman IPB, ulat bulu di daerah Probolinggo dan Jakarta itu berbeda spesies.">Though the facts of the expedition while the team of Plant Protection IPB, caterpillars in the region of Probolinggo and Jakarta are different species. <br /> <br /></span><span title="Ada berbagai dugaan faktor pemicu terjadinya ledakan ulat bulu di beberapa tempat.">There are various factors triggering allegations caterpillar explosion in some places. </span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Menurut Prof.">According to Prof. </span><span title="Dr.">Dr. </span><span title="Ir.">Ir. </span><span title="Aunu Rauf.">Aunu Rauf. </span><span title="MSc, salah satu faktornya adalah adanya musim hujan yang berkepanjangan mengakibatkan parasitoid atau musuh alami dari ulat bulu tidak mampu bertahan hidup, sehingga populasi ulat bulu meningkat drastis.">MSc, one factor is the prolonged rainy season resulted in parasitoids or natural enemy of caterpillars do not survive, so the caterpillar population has increased dramatically. </span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Selain itu, adanya migrasi ngengat (imago ulat bulu) dari habitatnya menuju pemukiman warga, karena habitat asalnya telah rusak.">In addition, the migration of moths (caterpillars imago) of habitat to residential, because the native habitat has been damaged. <br /> <br /></span><span title="Serangan ulat bulu ini telah mengakibatkan banyak pihak menjadi khawatir dan resah.">Caterpillar attack has resulted in many people become anxious and restless. </span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Berbagai upaya pengendalian telah dilakukan oleh warga, pemerintah daerah, dan beberapa instansi yang terkait, mulai dari pengendalian mekanis dengan diambil secara manual, pengendalian hayati dengan penggunaan predator, hingga pengendalian kimiawi dengan penyemprotan insektisida sintetik.">Various control measures have been carried out by citizens, local governments, and several related agencies, ranging from mechanical control to be taken manually, the use of biological control with predators, to control with chemical spraying of synthetic insecticides. <br /> <br /></span><span style="background-color: #ffffff;" title="Adanya fenomena ulat bulu ini bukanlah ancaman, tetapi menjadi tantangan bagi tim ekspedisi Proteksi Tanaman IPB untuk menemukan berbagai potensi pengendalian yang akan dipadukan dalam suatu pengendalian hama terpadu (PHT) yang efektif dalam mengendalikan hama ulat bulu dan aman bagi ekosistem alami.">The existence of this phenomenon caterpillar is not a threat but a challenge for Plant Protection IPB expedition team to find a variety of potential controls that will be integrated in an integrated pest management (IPM) is effective in controlling caterpillar pests and safe for natural ecosystems.</span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">(Herma Amalia)</span></p>', '2011-07-27 21:19:45', 1),
(31, 'Organisasi', 'Organization', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Organisasi</a></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Teks Indonesia</p>', '<h2 style="border-bottom: 2px solid #CCCCCC;"><img src="images/news.jpg" alt="" width="25" height="25" /><a href="#"> &nbsp;Organization</a></h2>\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2><strong><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">MANAGEMENT OF THE DEPARTMENT</span></strong></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">The Department of Plant Protection (DPP) is an implementation unit of the Faculty of Agriculture, Bogor Agricultural University, in executing higher education in the field of plant pests and diseases. However, under the total quality management approach adopted by the Faculty of Agriculture, the department has autonomy to exercise its own managerial and organizational approaches based on specific characteristics of human resources, facilities, and scientific domain and environment. The department is chaired by the head of department that is elected every four years. The latest election was held on September 2007 which was resulted the organization structure and management team of the DPP. The present organization structure reflects the development of the department mainly due to the implementation of the status of IPB as a legal entity institution (BHMN). The present management team of the department was actively in duties since December 2007. </span></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">The elected head of department is accountable in organizing structural and functional organization within the department to achieve the mission and objective. In conducting daily activities, the department head is assisted by two secretaries and one coordinator for each of facilities commission. There is also an Administration Office, that responsible for day to day activities of the departmental administration.</span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Educational and academic committee in the department consists of chairman of Entomology and Plant Pathology study program (graduate program), coordinator of academic affair, and coordinator of student and alumni affair. In line with the vision and mission of the department as stated earlier, the DPP become a home for three important units, i.e. Insect Museum, Plant Clinic, and Center for Integrated Pest Management. These units have specific scope of programs, and also function as Public Relations of the Department of PP and a bridge to establish collaboration between different institutions, both government and private, as well as national and international level. Additionally, it is envisaged that these units can also generate revenues for the DPP. There is also the Development Commission, whose main task is providing guidance for the DPP.</span></h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong>The personnel of the Department of Plant Protection - IPB (2007-2011)</strong></span></p>\n<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>\n<div align="center">\n<table style="width: 600px; height: 642px;" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;" valign="top" width="50%">\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong>Function</strong></span></p>\n</td>\n<td style="text-align: left;" valign="top" width="50%">\n<p align="center"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong>Personnel</strong></span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;" valign="top" width="50%">\n<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">Head</span></p>